# ArtifactGraph

- The docs repo is the full registry/parity hub. ArtifactGraph is installed
  there by default with `common,docs`.
- On FE/BE/tests, ArtifactGraph is local-only: use it only for that repo's own
  tag/allowlist hints. It does not follow `HUBDOCS_ROOT` or
  `CODEGENKIT_DOCS_ROOT`.
- FE generation that needs full docs IR/registries must use
  `CODEGENKIT_DOCS_ROOT`; Hubdocs ID lookups use `HUBDOCS_ROOT`.
- Config, local registries, templates, and lexicons remain repository-local.
- Use local analyze/grill/parity/suggest before requesting cloud work.
- Never dump full registries or lexicons into `cloudPromptSlice`.
- Run only generation keys allowlisted by the current repo.
- Promote canonical registry changes in the docs repo; promote repo-local
  allowlists/templates only in the current code/test repo.
- Do not depend on `platform-repos.json`, `base-docs`, or `base-tests`.

Hooks: `.cursor/extracts/artifactgraph-hooks-core.md`
